			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We can change the pexe wire format so that forward value references are listed at the start of a function.

This would mean that operands are consistently represented as a single field, instead of being 1 or 2 fields.  This would remove the distinction between getValueTypePair() and popValue() in the reader.

Motivation: Large reduction in the format's complexity.

(This task is from the list at https://docs.google.com/document/d/1HvZJVwS9KeTc0jUvoQjbLapRbStHk3mZ0rPDUHNN96Y/edit.)
